HEADWORD: Zigzaggery
<hw>Zig"zag`ger*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or
state of being zigzag; crookedness.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The . . . <qex>zigzaggery</qex> of my father's approaches.</q>
<rj><qau>Sterne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zigzaggy</ent>⟦br⟧
